This paper proposes a method for pruning deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. However, the paper also introduces a new type of parameter and regularization method, which may suggest that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The end-to-end training approach and the use of stochastic optimization methods may also suggest that it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, depending on the specific applications of the proposed method.
